<h4 id="-setup-shortcut-to-run-the-retro_typer-macos">â© Setup Shortcut to run the retro_typer (MACOS)</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Open the Shortcuts app in macos</li>
  <li>Click the plus button at the top right corner to add a new shortcut</li>
  <li>click on the search bar at the top right corner and type â€œOpen Appâ€ for the action. Drag open app to the main area.</li>
  <li>Click on the app keyword and find retro_typer</li>
  <li>To setup a keyboard shortcut, click the information icon at the top right corner of the shortcuts app.</li>
  <li>Click â€œAdd Keyboard Shortcutâ€ and add your shortcut key combination, you can press shift + option + e</li>
  <li>And youâ€™re done ! Just press the shortcut anywhere.</li>
</ol>

